---
import MainLayout from "~/layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import { Card, LargeTitleText } from "@origami-systems/ui";
import SupportEmail from "@/SupportEmail.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Terms of Use - The House App">
    <LargeTitleText>Terms of Use</LargeTitleText>
    <div class="acard">
        <Card>
            <div class="container">
                By using this app, you agree to the following terms:

                <h2>Purpose of the App</h2>
                This app is provided for use by schools, churches, and similar organizations
                to track and manage group participation and engagement.

                <h2>Your Responsibilities</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Use the app respectfully and for its intended purpose.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Do not attempt to bypass restrictions or access other
                        organizations’ data.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Do not share inappropriate content or misuse group
                        tools.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Account Access</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        You are responsible for keeping your login credentials
                        secure.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        If you’re using a shared (group) account, only use it as
                        directed by your organization.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Admin Rights</h2>
                Admins in your organization may view or manage your account, including
                assigning house, or removing access.

                <h2>Modifications to the Service</h2>
                We may update the app or these Terms at any time. In the event of
                major changes, we will provide reasonable notice through email or
                in-app messages.

                <h2>Termination</h2>
                We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate
                these terms or misuse the platform.

                <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
                The app is provided ‘as is’ without warranties of any kind, either
                express or implied. We do not guarantee uninterrupted service, and
                we are not liable for any outages, data loss, or errors caused by
                third-party systems.

                <h2>Governing Law</h2>
                These terms are governed by the laws of Texas.

                <h2>User Content</h2>
                You agree that content you submit complies with community standards
                and that the organization may moderate or remove inappropriate content.

                <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
                We are not liable for damages arising from use or inability to use
                the service.

                <h2>Contact</h2>
                Questions or issues? Email us at
                <SupportEmail />.
            </div>
        </Card>
    </div>
</MainLayout>

<style lang="scss">
    .acard {
        :global(.card) {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 700px;
        }
    }

    .container {
        text-align: left;
        counter-reset: section;
    }

    .container h2 {
        counter-increment: section;
        position: relative;
        padding-left: 2rem;
    }

    .container h2::before {
        content: counter(section) ".";
        position: absolute;
        left: 0;
        font-weight: 600;
    }
</style>
